<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-22T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-22T14:00:00-05:00" n="484" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d484">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">860c.01/6–2145: Telegram</note>
                                <head>No. 484<lb/><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting
                                            Secretary of State</gloss> to the Ambassador in the
                                        Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HK1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>)</head>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#left">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                        <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent—niact</hi>
                                    </seg>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-22T15:00:00-04:00">June 22, 1945—3 p.m.</date>
                                    </dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>1370. <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> concurs in your
                                    action as Commissioner in accepting the settlement.<note n="1" xml:id="d484fn1">See <ref target="#d486">document No.
                                            486</ref>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>For your information, I have telegraphed the President<note n="2" xml:id="d484fn2">Then at Olympia, Washington.</note> giving
                                    him an outline of your 2218, June 21,<note n="3" xml:id="d484fn3">Not printed.</note> regarding agreement on
                                    Polish Government. I have recommended that he give favorable
                                    consideration, if the British Government concurs, to grant
                                    recognition to the newly-constituted government as the new
                                    Polish Provisional Government of National Unity.</p>
                                <p>As soon as I hear from the President I shall inform you of his
                                    decision.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                                        </persName>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>